ZeroClaw Architecture Plan

Repository Shape
- Monorepo with Rust workspace plus a single SPA frontend.
- Root files:
  - Cargo.toml: workspace members and shared dependency versions.
  - Cargo.lock
  - README.md
  - .plan
- apps/api: Axum server binary crate.
- apps/web: React + Vite + Tailwind application.
- crates/domain: graph domain types, shared DTOs, query result types.
- crates/storage: Postgres repositories, migrations wiring, persistence models.
- crates/graph: in-memory petgraph index and traversal helpers.
- crates/query: mini-Cypher lexer, parser, AST, executor.
- crates/seed: seed script loading and reset helpers.
- crates/test-support: optional shared fixtures/utilities if repeated test setup appears.

Rust Module Layout
- apps/api/src/main.rs: bootstrap tracing, config, DB pool, graph state, router.
- apps/api/src/config.rs: env parsing and validated runtime config.
- apps/api/src/http/
  - mod.rs
  - health.rs
  - graph.rs
  - query.rs
  - seed.rs
  - export.rs
  - error.rs
- apps/api/src/state.rs: AppState with pool, repositories, graph index, seed services.
- apps/api/src/spa.rs: static asset serving for built frontend.
- crates/domain/src/
  - lib.rs
  - node.rs
  - relationship.rs
  - graph.rs
  - query_result.rs
- crates/storage/src/
  - lib.rs
  - postgres.rs
  - nodes.rs
  - relationships.rs
  - migrations/
- crates/graph/src/
  - lib.rs
  - index.rs
  - traversal.rs
- crates/query/src/
  - lib.rs
  - lexer.rs
  - parser.rs
  - ast.rs
  - executor.rs
  - error.rs
- crates/seed/src/
  - lib.rs
  - loader.rs
  - seed.cypher

Frontend Layout
- apps/web/src/
  - main.tsx
  - App.tsx
  - lib/api.ts
  - lib/queryClient.ts
  - hooks/
  - components/layout/
  - components/graph/
  - components/editor/
  - components/results/
  - components/inspector/
  - components/common/
  - types/api.ts
  - styles/
- Use TanStack Query for server state and Cytoscape for graph rendering.
- Keep app state thin in React: selected node/edge, query history, current result set, UI panel state.

Shared Types
- Domain crate owns canonical Node, Relationship, GraphSnapshot, QueryResult, QueryRow, and export payload shapes.
- API responses should serialize domain DTOs directly where possible to avoid duplicate backend/frontend mapping logic.
- Frontend should generate TS types from a hand-authored shared contract file or mirror stable DTOs in src/types/api.ts; keep naming aligned with Rust JSON payloads.

Key Design Decisions
- Use a Rust workspace from the start so API, domain, storage, graph, query, and seed logic remain independently testable.
- Keep the mini-Cypher engine separate from HTTP concerns; the API should call a query service instead of embedding parser/executor logic in handlers.
- Use Postgres as source of truth and rebuild or refresh the in-memory petgraph index from persisted data after mutating queries.
- Prefer transactional writes for CREATE and DETACH DELETE, then update the in-memory graph only after commit succeeds.
- Store node properties and relationship properties as JSONB for flexibility while keeping labels/type fields explicit for indexing and UI display.
- Use a single seed pathway: the reset endpoint should truncate/reset DB state and then execute the same seed.cypher script through the query engine.
- Build the SPA separately with Vite, then serve static assets from Axum for the self-hosted production bundle.

