Suggested Delivery Sequence
- Foundation: 1, 2, 3, 4, 7, 8, 9, 10
- Query engine: 11, 12, 16, 13, 14, 15, 17
- API and seed: 23, 24, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22
- Frontend foundation: 5, 6, 25, 26, 27, 28, 29, 30
- Frontend workflows: 31, 32, 33, 34, 35
- Hardening and release: 36, 37, 38, 39

Risk Areas To Watch
- Query semantics can drift if AST design is too narrow; define supported mini-Cypher grammar early and keep tests exhaustive.
- Synchronizing DB writes with the in-memory graph index needs a single consistency strategy from the start.
- Static asset serving for the SPA should be decided early enough that local dev and production build paths do not diverge.
- End-to-end tests should target the production-like served bundle, not only separate dev servers.
